description:
'''Los Melódicos''' are a [[Venezuela]]n band founded in 1958.
Los Melódicos play {{lang|es|[[música tropical]]}} (literally "tropical music"), a genre developed on the [[Caribbean]] coasts of Venezuela, Colombia, and other [[Central America]]n and Caribbean countries in the mid 20th century.{{r|wade}}

Los Melódicos are similar in style to fellow Venezuelan group [[Billo's Caracas Boys]], and were formed while [[Billo Frómeta]] was occupied by legal problems and unable to make music; Frómeta later wrote some arrangements for the band.{{r|wade}}
